<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 95-12-12 - Cylinder Head Bolt Torque Values And Instructions For T 444E Engine</stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi951212" tsitype="engine">
        <tsinumber>95-12-12</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>August, 1995</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>ENGINE</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Cylinder Head Bolt Torque Values And Instructions For T 444E Engine</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <engfamgroup/>

                <engfam>T 444E</engfam>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <svcproc svcproctype="TSI" graphiccount="2">
            <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
            <para>The cylinder head bolts are torqued in four stages as follows: (Note that Steps 1 &#38; 2 are in
                <emph type="italic">circular sequence</emph>
                and Step 3. is in
                <emph type="italic">linear sequence</emph>)
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Torque bolts to 54 N&#8226;m (40 lbf-ft) in
                    <emph type="bold">circular sequence</emph>
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9512121">shown below.</hotlnk>
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Torque bolts to 95 N&#8226;m (70 lbf-ft) in
                    <emph type="bold">circular sequence</emph>
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9512121">shown below.</hotlnk>
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9512121" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9512121.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 1.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">In linear sequence</emph>
                    Torque bolts to 129 N&#8226;m (95 lbf-ft) as
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9512122">shown below.</hotlnk>
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Repeat step #3.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9512122" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9512122.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 2.</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>THIS PROCEDURE SUPERSEDES TORQUE VALUES AND INSTRUCTIONS GIVEN IN ENGINE SERVICE MANUAL FORM
                        EGES-120. KEEP A COPY OF THIS SERVICE LETTER WITH THE MANUAL UNTIL IT IS REVISED.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcproc>
    </tsi>
</isis>
